{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/26/comments/74008475.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/diff/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo:821b79a7f8af..41f16f8b479b?path=src%2FServerPrivate.cc"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/26/_/diff#comment-74008475"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 26, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/26.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/26"}}, "title": "System plugins"}, "content": {"raw": "Not sure if you already have plans for this, but it should be totally doable within the current SDF spec if we use `name` as `alias`, for example:\n\n~~~\n<world name=\"world1\">\n  <plugin\n    name=\"MyCoolSystem\" \n    filename\"libMyCoolSystem.so\" \n    classname=\"my::cool::System\" \n    type=\"\"ignition::gazebo::System\"\n  />\n</world>\n~~~", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Not sure if you already have plans for this, but it should be totally doable within the current SDF spec if we use <code>name</code> as <code>alias</code>, for example:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"nt\">&lt;world</span> <span class=\"na\">name=</span><span class=\"s\">&quot;world1&quot;</span><span class=\"nt\">&gt;</span>\n  <span class=\"nt\">&lt;plugin</span>\n    <span class=\"na\">name=</span><span class=\"s\">&quot;MyCoolSystem&quot;</span> \n    <span class=\"err\">filename&quot;libMyCoolSystem.so&quot;</span> \n    <span class=\"na\">classname=</span><span class=\"s\">&quot;my::cool::System&quot;</span> \n    <span class=\"na\">type=</span><span class=\"s\">&quot;&quot;</span><span class=\"err\">ignition::gazebo::System&quot;</span>\n  <span class=\"nt\">/&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/world&gt;</span>\n</pre></div>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-08-24T19:14:28.50